The paper discusses the inefficiencies of current MapReduce implementations and proposes an automatic optimization tool called Manimal. The paper focuses on optimizing data operations, which is a core aspect of database systems (cs.DB). The optimization tool also involves analyzing and manipulating data structures, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of Java code, which is a programming language (cs.PL), and discusses the benefits of not requiring additional help from the programmer, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE).
